text:
I am a big Mario Batali fan and have really enjoyed some of his other establishments such as Eataly and Mozza, but Carnevino left me wanting more.

// LOCATION // In the Palazzo at the entrance of the casino on the strip so no need to walk deep into the casino to find it. 

// FOOD //
     + Ricotta and egg ravioli: Beautiful ravioli, but the 1 large ravioli I received for the small portion could not justify the anything but small price tag
     + Porterhouse: Tried a bit of the porterhouse, but it lacked flavor and did not pack the punch you would imagine steak would at a steakhouse.
